snippet.textDisplay: Microsoft didn't give Linux any love. They're aware of the scientific community exclusively using Linux systems, and in order to get in on the action, they're required to support GPU acceleration through their WSL2 system, which they are attempting to implement by adding a Linux accel driver that acts merely as a pipe between graphical applications on Linux and DirectX12 on the Windows host system, to avoid dedicating the GPU to the WSL2 system and instead provide a somewhat "shared" GPU.
